    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, can you help me understand the difference between a \"confidentiality period\" and a \"survival clause\" in a standard contract? I'm trying to make sure I don't miss anything important.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A **confidentiality period** dictates how long you must keep specific information secret after a contract ends. In contrast, a **survival clause** specifies which specific contractual obligations, like confidentiality or payment terms, continue to be legally effective long after the main agreement has terminated. Think of the survival clause as the mechanism that forces the obligations, such as the confidentiality, to stick around.",
      "source": "target",
