    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. I'm actually looking at a specific section in an NDA right now about \"indemnification.\" It's a bit dense. Can you explain what an indemnification clause actually means for my personal liability if something goes wrong? I want to know if there are any \"hidden\" risks I should be looking out for.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Indemnification is essentially a promise by one party (the indemnifying party) to cover the financial losses, damages, or legal costs incurred by the other party (the indemnitee). For your personal liability, you must check *who* is promising to protect *whom*. A hidden risk is if you are agreeing to indemnify the other party for *their own negligence*, rather than just issues arising from your actions.",
      "source": "target",
